<dl id="n40040c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40040c">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40040c"> 40(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tearer of work</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The common notions of the devil as black, ill-favoured, malicious, destructive and the like, have occasioned the application of the term to &hellip; mechanical contrivances (for tearing up cloth or separating wool) &hellip; <small> &ldquo;DEVIL&rdquo; <a name="EBDV" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDV"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) VIII 121</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
